"Role: As our Lead QA Engineer, you'll take the wheel in ensuring quality is driven into the heart of all development processes throughout the company from requirement definitions through to delivery of releases in the production environment. Specifically, with your knowledge of investing methodologies and principles, you'll help identify and address potential risks to the process, employ QA best practices throughout the team, and break large and complex testing/automation problems into smaller, actionable steps forward for the team. Your efforts will ensure that all developmental and QA processes within The company are significantly streamlined and that every product and service produced is of the utmost quality for our users to enjoy. You will work closely with the engineering team and product team to identify, document, and iron out bugs in the product. We sincerely believe that behind every successful product, there is a careful QA team. Hence you will have a significant role to play in stable and quality product releases. Responsibilities Develop a test plan for existing and upcoming features and products. Perform product testing and communicate results to key stakeholders. Work closely with the development and product teams to ensure smooth and timely releases Work in collaboration with developers to identify and solve bugs. Set up build automation and other automated testing methods (e.g. load testing, e2e testing, unit testing, integration testing). Own quality testing before each release. Work closely with our support and customer success team to deploy releases to customers. Own tier 3 tech support to troubleshoot issues in the field and guide technical support teams. Actively contribute to setting up good company quality processes and goals within the company. Grow the QA team by mentoring existing team members and recruiting new members as we scale up. Work with our engineering and product team to develop test plans, validate test fixtures and oversee all quality processes. Diagnose functional issues, report bugs, and take ownership of issue resolution. Key Requirement Being proactive and able to work independently. Excellent written and verbal communication skills. Experience working in an Agile/Scrum development process Solid in-depth knowledge of Quality Assurance principles and methodology, as well as knowledge of object-oriented design principles. Knowledge of modern best practices for professional software development including coding standards, code reviews, source control management, build processes, testing, and operations. Strong organizational and problem-solving skills with great attention to detail, including the ability to track multiple test executions simultaneously and synthesize the results. Experience in Javascript and Cypress Experience with test frameworks (e.g. Selenium, Robot) Experience with load testing and knowledge of load testing tools like Jmeter would be a plus. Open to All nationalities What you'll get: A competitive salary and many new opportunities More responsibilities and greater recognition for the work you do The opportunity to be a part of a lively and international development team A pioneering mindset shaped by a challenging and innovative work environment APPLY NOW SHARE THIS POST "
